                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, pink</seg>
                        <date>20th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ገ፡ አጽባሃ፡</abbr> for <expan>ገብረ፡ አጽባሃ፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#3rb">3rb</locus>, 45vb, 57rb, 57va)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist; a few lines
                           on the incipit page, alternating with black lines; incipit of the
                           subsections; elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the punctuation
                           signs and text dividers.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Fols. 77v: Crude drawing of a human (perhaps St. Kiros) in red pen; legend: ቅዱስ፡ አቡነ፡ ኪሮስ፡. - Omitted words or letters inserted interlineally in a secondary hand in blue ballpoint pen: e.g., fols. 6vb, 9ra, 13ra, 13vb, 15va, 30va, or in the main hand: fols. 4rb, 14ra, 31ra, 38rb, 64va. - Immediate corrections marked by thin lines above and below the word: fols. 7vb, 13ra. - Compressed script: fols. 69vb, 70rab. - Scribbles and doodles: <locus target="#45v">fol.  45v</locus>.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards covered with reddish-brown tooled
                           leather. 
 Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="leather"/>
                           <material key="wood"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">Two pairs of chains of endband stitches
                           at the spine cover.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">Blind tooled ornament on the leather cover (at least 6
                           tools were used: double line fillet, double circle, cross hatching,
                           triple line fillet, triple sine wave, single line fillet).</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
